HEADWORD: Optometer
<hw>Op*tom"e*ter</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Opt</ets>ic
+ <ets>-meter</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>An instrument for
measuring the distance of distinct vision, mainly for the selection of
eveglasses.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

